{
  "texts": [
    "A to H if there are 8 available answers, or 0 to 9 if there are 10 numeric answers.",
    "Accordingly, the prompt must have categorical answer start with a letter, and each numeric one with a digit from 0 to 9 (we used the same prompts in FA experiments for comparability).",
    "Note that in contrast with FA, this a deterministic process, as the probabilities for the single next token are always the same for a given prompt; furthermore, it removes the need for full-text generation hyper-parameters such as temperature, top-k, top-p, etc.",
    "Furthermore, when taking into account that, with a limited number of context questions, there are many duplicated socio-demographic profiles (and thus prompts) in actual surveys, full answer generation might be implemented in two different ways.",
    "Either we generate a single LLM answer for each individual in the survey, or we generate a fixed number of LLM answers (say 30 or 100, a number deemed sufficient to obtain good enough answer distributions) for each profile in the survey."
  ]
}